.SH "NAME"
fc_remove_host \- called to terminate any fc_transport\-related elements for a scsi host\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ fc_remove_host('u
.BI "void fc_remove_host(struct\ Scsi_Host\ *\ " "shost" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIshost\fR
.RS 4
Which
Scsi_Host
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
This routine is expected to be called immediately preceding the a driver\*(Aqs call to
\fBscsi_remove_host\fR\&.
.PP
WARNING: A driver utilizing the fc_transport, which fails to call this routine prior to
\fBscsi_remove_host\fR, will leave dangling objects in /sys/class/fc_remote_ports\&. Access to any of these objects can result in a system crash !!!
.SH "NOTES"
.PP
This routine assumes no locks are held on entry\&.
